    {
      "id": "1295177536002850906",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-14T09:13:07.818+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "A very good act 1 pick, when you still have all 4 of your strikes, and really want to deal burst damage. Falls off pretty hard after that, as most of the time you will want to be removing your strikes when possible, and your deck is larger and you are less likely to draw the right cards together. Has notable synergy with high caliber, high noon, bruise, vulnerable, strength, coalescence, and especially fully loaded. The damage is pretty solid, and I like taking this card to pick off act 1 elites, it’s very good into all 3, though notably any strikes it plays will hit random targets, which can be awkward into AOE fights like tri-sentries. Having your starting memento can also really help this explode for massive damage. \n\nThis does “play” the strikes, which works the way you want it to with ninja relics like shuriken and kunai, and will stack up nunchaku, ink bottle and pen nib faster (though that can also cause pen nib to get used on a basic if you aren’t careful). Playing out the strikes also has negative implications for time eater and the heart, though you’re not really expecting a card like this to do well in those fights anyways, and it’s done its job already by then. The main problem is that it just doesn’t do very much in the late game, but as long as you are aware of that when you pick it and draft accordingly, you will be fine. Even with its many positive traits, once you have your frontloaded damage in place and can clear short hallway fights effectively, there usually isn’t room to take a card like this, so I rarely take it outside of early act 1, or sometimes early act 2 if I’m stuck on 3 energy and haven’t been able to remove any strikes yet (a place you are really hoping to avoid). Quite good alongside runic pyramid to cheaply free up hand space by playing out your strikes, and to manage being on 3 energy more easily. The base rate of 9 damage is respectable, and you get 15 for 1 if you have even 1 strike in hand.",
      "author": {
        "id": "303064746129752074",
        "name": "kiku_katsumi",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Kiku",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/303064746129752074/52a9271c83d647c231c0cfb10f14cf83.png?size=512"
      },
      "attachments": [],
      "embeds": [],
      "stickers": [],
      "reactions": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "1295178760630308865",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-14T09:17:59.792+09:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Pairing it with lots of card draw (especially high noon) lets you line it up more often, though it still usually underperforms in the late game. The upgrade is fine at a standard +3. Retain was certainly cool and exciting, but made lining it up too easy.",
